1
00:01:34,280 --> 00:01:39,950
[The Story of Xing Fu]

2
00:01:40,050 --> 00:01:42,950
[Episode 39]

3
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:44,140
Xingyun,

4
00:01:44,590 --> 00:01:46,420
you're not young anymore.

5
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:47,780
You can't be busy

6
00:01:47,780 --> 00:01:49,670
with work all day.

7
00:01:49,670 --> 00:01:51,060
You should get a boyfriend.

8
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:54,590
Otherwise, you'll have
a hard time having children later.

9
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:55,860
Mom,

10
00:01:56,470 --> 00:01:57,470
I'm so busy.

11
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:59,110
I don't have free time at all.

12
00:02:00,950 --> 00:02:01,950
Gosh.

13
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,220
Look at you.

14
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,470
You are no busier than your sister.

15
00:02:07,670 --> 00:02:08,700
Look at Xingfu.

16
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:11,190
She is the head of the company,

17
00:02:11,190 --> 00:02:12,110
runs an inn,

18
00:02:12,390 --> 00:02:14,190
and has a family of elderly and children.

19
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:15,550
She got married

20
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:16,750
and gave birth to her child.

21
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,030
She didn't delay anything.

22
00:02:18,750 --> 00:02:20,540
Yeah, I'm wondering about that too.

23
00:02:20,660 --> 00:02:23,030
Mom, why does my sister have so much energy?

24
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,620
I'm as tired as a dog

25
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:26,870
when I get home

26
00:02:27,100 --> 00:02:28,820
from work every day,

27
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,060
and I don't want to do anything but sleep.

28
00:02:31,940 --> 00:02:34,270
Who knows what you've been up to all day?

29
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:36,030
And you still keep saying you're tired.

30
00:02:36,710 --> 00:02:38,340
I'm really tired.

31
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,190
Mom, I'm back.

32
00:02:41,820 --> 00:02:42,150
Xingfu.

33
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:42,910
You're back.

34
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:43,870
You haven't eaten, have you?

35
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:44,660
Perfect timing.

36
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:45,220
Come and have some noodles.

37
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:47,620
Why do you want to see me?

38
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:49,430
Did Wan Chuanjia tell you to see me?

39
00:02:49,940 --> 00:02:50,940
If it's about Shuiwei Village,

40
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:52,030
you can't forget about it.

41
00:02:52,590 --> 00:02:53,030
Xingfu,

42
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:55,100
I was talking to Mom about you.

43
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:56,430
I wonder

44
00:02:56,430 --> 00:02:57,660
how you can be so energetic all day long.

45
00:02:58,190 --> 00:02:59,870
You have a hand in everything.

46
00:03:00,940 --> 00:03:03,380
It's not our business,

47
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,270
why do you care about other people's business?

48
00:03:05,470 --> 00:03:06,310
All right, stop it.

49
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:07,310
I know what you want to say.

50
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:10,870
I'm really not here to advise you
on anyone else's behalf.

51
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,150
We are sisters.

52
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:14,780
I'm doing this for your sake.

53
00:03:15,620 --> 00:03:16,590
I am sincerely advising you.

54
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:18,220
It's none of your business,

55
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:20,100
and there's no need to offend so many people.

56
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:21,340
Why do you have to do that?

57
00:03:24,590 --> 00:03:25,190
Xingyun,

58
00:03:25,620 --> 00:03:27,060
I'm tired of repeating myself to you.

59
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:29,270
But I advise you

60
00:03:29,590 --> 00:03:31,030
that although you are their lawyer,

61
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:31,990
if they have done

62
00:03:31,990 --> 00:03:33,340
something unethical,

63
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:35,190
you must stick to

64
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:36,620
your principles and bottom line

65
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:38,030
and not be complicit

66
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:38,940
in their actions.

67
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:40,590
Xingyun,

68
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,870
Xingfu is right.

69
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:43,990
You must listen to her.

70
00:03:44,540 --> 00:03:45,910
Mom, you don't know anything.

71
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:48,190
Why do you agree with her?

72
00:03:49,750 --> 00:03:50,270
Xingfu,

73
00:03:50,780 --> 00:03:53,310
what if you're wrong?

74
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:55,870
I wish I'm wrong.

75
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,190
I wish they didn't do it.

76
00:03:57,820 --> 00:03:59,150
What if I'm right?

77
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,710
All the more reason for you to stay out of it.

78
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,990
Do you know what it would mean

79
00:04:02,990 --> 00:04:04,310
if they did cause personal injury

80
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:04,820
and pollution

81
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:05,310
by

82
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,150
illegally discharging wastewater?

83
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,030
The perpetrator of the crime

84
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:09,340
is to be sentenced to prison.

85
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:11,380
Can they not fight with you?

86
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:17,990
I really don't mean to scare you.

87
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:19,060
Mr. Han

88
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:20,340
is a vicious person.

89
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:22,820
I really don't know what kind of
bad ideas he can come up with.

90
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:24,430
The shot hits the bird that pokes its head out.

91
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,750
Stay out of it, will you?

92
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:27,630
Xingfu.

93
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:29,540
If that's the case,

94
00:04:29,590 --> 00:04:31,150
let them press charges if they want to.

95
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:32,100
Yes.

96
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:34,390
Don't get involved in this.

97
00:04:34,660 --> 00:04:35,270
Okay?

98
00:05:04,510 --> 00:05:05,660
You heartless betrayer.

99
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:07,860
I'll smash you to death!

100
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:10,100
Coward!

101
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,270
Don't run if you have guts!

102
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:30,590
Are you okay?

103
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,070
Why are you here?

104
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:35,710
I...

105
00:05:36,510 --> 00:05:37,300
I'm passing by.

106
00:05:40,860 --> 00:05:41,910
You're bleeding.

107
00:05:42,860 --> 00:05:43,980
Get to the hospital now.

108
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,220
Nothing serious.

109
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,100
Just a minor injury.

110
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:52,270
When you get home,

111
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:53,100
rest well

112
00:05:53,390 --> 00:05:54,150
and keep the wound away from water.

113
00:05:55,780 --> 00:05:56,180
Okay.

114
00:05:56,180 --> 00:05:56,780
I got it.

115
00:05:58,470 --> 00:05:59,980
Did you see the man who hit you?

116
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:04,980
No.

117
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,710
But I know why they hit me.

118
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:11,150
Why?

119
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:15,660
Because I am helping the people
of Shuiwei Village to sue them,

120
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:17,070
and that conflicts with their interests.

121
00:06:19,980 --> 00:06:21,830
So don't you hate the people who hurt you?

122
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:23,420
Why should I hate them?

123
00:06:24,630 --> 00:06:25,910
That's because they all don't know it.

124
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:28,340
I believe

125
00:06:28,660 --> 00:06:30,420
that they will understand one day

126
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:32,470
that I am actually doing it
for the good of everyone.

127
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,740
So I understand that they hold a grudge

128
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:36,740
against me now.

129
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:42,420
Gang should get married earlier.

130
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:44,100
I'm so worried.

131
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,270
I can't find a good match for him.

132
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:46,390
I'm really worried.

133
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:48,590
I envy you.

134
00:06:51,740 --> 00:06:53,300
I think she's back. Let me take a look.

135
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:57,630
Xingfu,

136
00:06:58,710 --> 00:06:59,590
Gang's mother is here.

137
00:06:59,660 --> 00:07:00,630
She said she wanted to see you.

138
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:09,340
Xingfu.

139
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:10,150
Madam.

140
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:11,980
What happened to you?

141
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:13,220
Nothing.

142
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,590
Someone threw stones at me.

143
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:15,830
Sit down.

144
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,780
Is this serious?

145
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:17,950
Who's so immoral?

146
00:07:18,030 --> 00:07:18,980
How did they throw the stones?

147
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:20,300
What if you are badly hurt?

148
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:22,470
It's okay, Mom. The doctor has dressed it up.

149
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,100
Nothing serious.

150
00:07:23,270 --> 00:07:24,950
This must be a deliberate act of evil.

151
00:07:25,270 --> 00:07:26,270
How immoral.

152
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:27,780
Madam,

153
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:28,910
what can I do for you?

154
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:32,660
I just want to persuade you

155
00:07:33,510 --> 00:07:34,630
not to bother about

156
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:36,340
Shuiwei Village.

157
00:07:36,780 --> 00:07:39,180
Now everyone is hoping that Wan Village

158
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:41,630
will win the Entrepreneurship
in Rural Communities Competition.

159
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:43,390
When Wan Village becomes famous,

160
00:07:43,510 --> 00:07:45,180
those of us who run homestay businesses
can benefit from it.

161
00:07:45,630 --> 00:07:46,830
But if you take the case to court,

162
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:48,660
you'll ruin it

163
00:07:48,910 --> 00:07:50,540
and everyone won't get a fortune out of it.

164
00:07:51,910 --> 00:07:52,740
Madam,

165
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,340
tell everyone

166
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:56,780
that if the water is good, the fish can be kept,

167
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:58,980
but if the water is polluted, no fish can be kept.

168
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:02,630
You're right.

169
00:08:03,470 --> 00:08:05,070
But how can we talk about the future

170
00:08:05,100 --> 00:08:06,510
when we can't even take care
of things at the moment?

171
00:08:06,910 --> 00:08:08,420
Alright, stop it.

172
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,070
Protect yourself first.

173
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:11,590
Go back to your room and rest.

174
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:12,510
Yes.

175
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:13,510
Go and lie down now.

176
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:14,950
Don't go out in the next couple of days.

177
00:08:16,470 --> 00:08:17,270
What happened?

178
00:08:17,980 --> 00:08:18,660
Nothing.

179
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:19,710
What nothing?

180
00:08:19,710 --> 00:08:20,510
Someone threw stones at her.

181
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,910
It's about Shuiwei Village.

182
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,630
Stay out of this from now on.

183
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:27,150
Nothing serious.

184
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,100
Qinglai.

185
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:33,270
Qinglai, where are you going? Qinglai!

186
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:35,540
Mr. Wan!

187
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:36,100
Coming.

188
00:08:36,300 --> 00:08:37,780
Who is it? It's late at night!

189
00:08:38,630 --> 00:08:39,100
Coming.

190
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:40,220
Mr. Wan.

191
00:08:42,580 --> 00:08:42,910
Qinglai.

192
00:08:42,910 --> 00:08:43,990
Chuanjia, I want to see Mr. Wan.

193
00:08:44,580 --> 00:08:45,060
He's inside.

194
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:45,940
Mr. Wan.

195
00:08:46,350 --> 00:08:47,540
-What happened?
-Qinglai.

196
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:48,150
Mr. Wan.

197
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:49,420
What's wrong?

198
00:08:50,110 --> 00:08:51,820
Someone threw stones at Xingfu.

199
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:53,300
Are you going to take care of this?

200
00:08:53,510 --> 00:08:53,820
This...

201
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:55,060
If you don't take care of it,
I'll take care of it myself.

202
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:57,180
Even if I have to turn the Wan Village upside down,

203
00:08:57,180 --> 00:08:58,350
I have to find this person.

204
00:08:58,750 --> 00:08:59,660
I'll give him a taste

205
00:08:59,820 --> 00:09:00,780
of what it's like

206
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:02,180
to be smashed with stones in the dark.

207
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,300
No... When did it happen?

208
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:04,390
Just now.

209
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:06,270
I know that Xingfu

210
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:07,750
is helping the people of Shuiwei Village

211
00:09:08,180 --> 00:09:09,060
to bring a lawsuit against the factory.

212
00:09:09,060 --> 00:09:10,060
Someone's mad at her.

213
00:09:10,580 --> 00:09:12,540
But we can talk about it.

214
00:09:13,230 --> 00:09:15,030
Why threw stones at her?

215
00:09:19,270 --> 00:09:20,780
You... Don't... Don't be mad.

216
00:09:20,780 --> 00:09:21,420
Qinglai.

217
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,540
Do you know who did it?

218
00:09:23,030 --> 00:09:24,150
I don't know.

219
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:25,460
Find out who did this at once!

220
00:09:26,510 --> 00:09:27,990
How wicked!

221
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:31,910
Wan Village

222
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,350
is a model village in the province

223
00:09:33,350 --> 00:09:34,060
and a civilized village.

224
00:09:34,350 --> 00:09:36,030
How dare someone do such a dirty act?

225
00:09:36,230 --> 00:09:36,940
What's it?

226
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:38,420
This is a disgrace to the village officers

227
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:39,990
and to the villagers as a whole.

228
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:41,110
Alright.

229
00:09:41,230 --> 00:09:42,510
Calm down.

230
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:43,510
I'll investigate it.

231
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:44,870
Qinglai, don't worry.

232
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:45,460
I know about this.

233
00:09:45,460 --> 00:09:46,540
I'll definitely get to the bottom of it.

234
00:09:47,110 --> 00:09:48,030
But you should go back

235
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:49,300
and talk to Xingfu too.

236
00:09:49,940 --> 00:09:51,390
I guess someone who's just pissed off

237
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:51,750
and that he...

238
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:52,460
Who's pissed off?

239
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:53,350
Who?

240
00:09:53,870 --> 00:09:55,420
How do I know who's pissed off?

241
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:57,150
I'm just guessing.

242
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:58,270
Then, I'll see

243
00:09:58,350 --> 00:10:00,110
who the person you guess is.

244
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,420
I wanted to try to

245
00:10:02,990 --> 00:10:04,300
mediate this matter

246
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,580
and not take it to court.

247
00:10:05,910 --> 00:10:06,660
In this case,

248
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:08,270
they have my support in taking the case to court.

249
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:09,820
I just want to see

250
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:11,940
if there's anything untoward going on here.

251
00:10:16,510 --> 00:10:17,180
Come closer.

252
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:19,270
What's wrong?

253
00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:20,630
Come.

254
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,700
Stamped. A reward for you.

255
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:26,350
You know to protect your wife now.

256
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,350
Don't worry.

257
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:29,580
With me around,

258
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:32,780
no one will bully my wife and kid.

259
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:34,510
You're arrogant after being complimented.

260
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,060
Anyway,

261
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:37,990
you didn't have to

262
00:10:37,990 --> 00:10:39,030
go to Mr. Wan.

263
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,460
How about I go to Mr. Wan tomorrow

264
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:43,820
and tell him to let it go?

265
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:45,780
Since I already got smashed

266
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:46,630
and it's nothing serious,

267
00:10:46,870 --> 00:10:47,700
don't investigate it.

268
00:10:48,540 --> 00:10:49,270
But why?

269
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:52,580
Because I don't want to make a big deal out of it.

270
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:55,630
The main purpose of the lawsuit is
to find out the source of the pollution,

271
00:10:55,630 --> 00:10:56,580
nothing more.

272
00:10:57,350 --> 00:10:58,060
I know.

273
00:10:59,460 --> 00:10:59,940
But

274
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,940
it's outrageous that someone

275
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:03,940
would do something like this.

276
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:07,580
Even Mr. Wan thinks there's
something fishy going on here.

277
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:10,110
He also said

278
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:11,990
he supports the people from Shuiwei Village
to take the case to court.

279
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:14,150
He did?

280
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:15,700
Why would I lie to you?

281
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:20,460
Before you came back,

282
00:11:21,510 --> 00:11:22,460
I was worried

283
00:11:22,460 --> 00:11:23,940
if I was really being nosy,

284
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,030
if I was really doing something wrong.

285
00:11:27,110 --> 00:11:28,270
What made you think so?

